<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ee80674e-d1d4-43f7-b361-f9316d12e132" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>G7D2</sptc><title id="_9c509a55-0d88-4431-a810-67f5bb151007">Livable housing design</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_a0ad0da0-fe16-47f8-8928-448aa06ee602" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e9dae0f7-9f7e-49a4-85f3-968f031ece53">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Each <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_e61382e7-f434-438f-8ac9-7499a7894fa5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> in a Class 2 building must comply with the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design, except for Part 1.</p></subclause><callout id="_b2d73abe-be68-441b-9c9f-eaff27580ba1"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>Part 1 of the <xref format="html" href="https://abcb.gov.au/sites/default/files/resources/2023/livable-housing-design-20230406.pdf" id="_f69c8c27-4cd7-4219-a034-81b231f99ef3" scope="external">ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design</xref> requires a step-free access path from a parking space or property boundary, to the dwelling entry door. For Class 2 buildings, this requirement is already addressed by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/26_0.10.0.xml#_0422da33-ebd2-4d7c-994c-31d8dad5aa0f" id="_031ea7e3-7cbe-43c6-9ab6-6c441bb1e0b2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-part">Part D4</xref> and the Disability (Access to Premisesâ€”Buildings) Standards 2010. Therefore, it is not necessary to apply Part 1 of the ABCB Standard for Livable Housing Design to a Class 2 building.</p></callout></clause>